9// *** NOTE: This file is #included into the middle of the target
10// *** instruction selector class. These functions are really methods.
11
12// If GET_DAGISEL_DECL is #defined with any value, only function
13// declarations will be included when this file is included.
14// If GET_DAGISEL_BODY is #defined, its value should be the name of
15// the instruction selector class. Function bodies will be emitted
16// and each function's name will be qualified with the name of the
17// class.
18//
19// When neither of the GET_DAGISEL* macros is defined, the functions
20// are emitted inline.
21
22#if defined(GET_DAGISEL_DECL) && defined(GET_DAGISEL_BODY)
23#error GET_DAGISEL_DECL and GET_DAGISEL_BODY cannot be both defined, undef both for inline definitions
24#endif
25
26#ifdef GET_DAGISEL_BODY
27#define LOCAL_DAGISEL_STRINGIZE(X) LOCAL_DAGISEL_STRINGIZE_(X)
28#define LOCAL_DAGISEL_STRINGIZE_(X) #X
29static_assert(sizeof(LOCAL_DAGISEL_STRINGIZE(GET_DAGISEL_BODY)) > 1,
30 "GET_DAGISEL_BODY is empty: it should be defined with the class name");
31#undef LOCAL_DAGISEL_STRINGIZE_
32#undef LOCAL_DAGISEL_STRINGIZE
33#endif
34
35#if !defined(GET_DAGISEL_DECL) && !defined(GET_DAGISEL_BODY)
36#define DAGISEL_INLINE 1
37#else
38#define DAGISEL_INLINE 0
39#endif
40
41#if !DAGISEL_INLINE
42#define DAGISEL_CLASS_COLONCOLON GET_DAGISEL_BODY ::
43#else
44#define DAGISEL_CLASS_COLONCOLON
45#endif

3602 case 1:

3605 }
3606}
3607#endif // GET_DAGISEL_BODY
3608
3609#ifdef GET_DAGISEL_DECL
3610SDValue RunSDNodeXForm(SDValue V, unsigned XFormNo) override;
3611#endif
3612#if defined(GET_DAGISEL_BODY) || DAGISEL_INLINE
3613SDValue DAGISEL_CLASS_COLONCOLON RunSDNodeXForm(SDValue V, unsigned XFormNo)
3614#if DAGISEL_INLINE
3615 override
3616#endif
3617{
3618 switch (XFormNo) {
3619 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid xform # in table?");
3620 case 0: { // HI22_not
3621 ConstantSDNode *N = cast<ConstantSDNode>(V.getNode());
3622
3623 return CurDAG->getTargetConstant(~(unsigned)N->getZExtValue() >> 10, SDLoc(N),
3624 MVT::i32);
3625
3626 }
3627 case 1: { // as_i32imm
3628 ConstantSDNode *N = cast<ConstantSDNode>(V.getNode());
3629
3630 return CurDAG->getTargetConstant(N->getSExtValue(), SDLoc(N), MVT::i32);
3631
3632 }
3633 case 2: { // HI22
3634 ConstantSDNode *N = cast<ConstantSDNode>(V.getNode());
3635
3636 // Transformation function: shift the immediate value down into the low bits.
3637 return CurDAG->getTargetConstant((unsigned)N->getZExtValue() >> 10, SDLoc(N),
3638 MVT::i32);
3639
3640 }
3641 case 3: { // LO10
3642 ConstantSDNode *N = cast<ConstantSDNode>(V.getNode());
3643
3644 return CurDAG->getTargetConstant((unsigned)N->getZExtValue() & 1023, SDLoc(N),
3645 MVT::i32);
3646
3647 }
3648 case 4: { // HIX22
3649 ConstantSDNode *N = cast<ConstantSDNode>(V.getNode());
3650
3651 uint64_t Val = (~N->getZExtValue() >> 10) & ((1u << 22) - 1);
3652 return CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Val, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32);
3653
3654 }
3655 case 5: { // LOX10
3656 ConstantSDNode *N = cast<ConstantSDNode>(V.getNode());
3657
3658 return CurDAG->getTargetConstant(~(~N->getZExtValue() & 0x3ff), SDLoc(N),
3659 MVT::i32);
3660
3661 }
3662 case 6: { // HH22
3663 ConstantSDNode *N = cast<ConstantSDNode>(V.getNode());
3664
3665 uint64_t Val = (N->getZExtValue() >> 42) & ((1u << 22) - 1);
3666 return CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Val, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32);
3667
3668 }
3669 case 7: { // HM10
3670 ConstantSDNode *N = cast<ConstantSDNode>(V.getNode());
3671
3672 uint64_t Val = (N->getZExtValue() >> 32) & ((1u << 10) - 1);
3673 return CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Val, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32);
3674
3675 }
3676 }
3677}
3678#endif // GET_DAGISEL_BODY
